.TH HSH 1 "November 2025" "Simple Shell" "User Commands"
.SH NAME
hsh - Simple command-line interpreter
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B hsh
.SH DESCRIPTION
.B hsh
is a simple UNIX command interpreter (shell) that reads commands from standard input, executes them, and waits for them to complete. It mimics the basic functionality of the Bourne shell (sh).
.PP
The shell displays a prompt "($) " and waits for a command. A command line is terminated by a new line.
.PP
In non-interactive mode (e.g., \fBecho "ls" | ./hsh\fR), it executes the command(s) and exits.
.SH COMMAND HANDLING
.IP
1.
Reads a line from standard input.
.IP
2.
Parses the line into a command and arguments.
.IP
3.
Checks if the command is a built-in (\fBexit\fR, \fBenv\fR).
.IP
4.
If not a built-in, it searches for the executable in the directories specified by the \fBPATH\fR environment variable.
.IP
5.
Executes the command in a child process using \fBexecve(2)\fR.
.SH BUILT-IN COMMANDS
.TP
.B exit
Exit the shell. The shell exits with a status of 0.
.TP
.B env
Print the current environment variables, one per line.
.SH EXIT STATUS
.B hsh
returns the exit status of the last command executed.
.SH AUTHORS
Written by the authors listed in the AUTHORS file.
